{
  "stem": "11611.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was, but kind of marginally in college.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the-- in the late '30s, there was a big student organization, national in character, called the American Student Union.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Around 1939, it split.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it really split because there was some general feeling that the communists had taken it over at that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was around the time, I think-- I'm not sure of the exact dates, but I think 1940 was the year that the Soviet Union invaded Finland, which seemed to produce a lot of agitation.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I went with the split-off group, which was anti-communist, which-- which got-- I can't remember exactly the name of it, but I think it became National Student something to distinguish itself from the ASU.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was educated at the University of Chicago.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Obviously, I was a right-winger in those days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The University of Chicago never produced anything but right-wingers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, my family, like all immigrant families, would-- voted Democratic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I had great doubts that the Democrats were on the path to virtue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the University of Chicago, 1939.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yeah, going back and forth to classes, listening to lectures, like Edward Benes, who was at the University of Chicago in '39.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Professor Benes had been prime minister or president-- I forget what the title was-- of Czechoslovakia when the Germans marched which was 1939.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans moved into Czechoslovakia in March 1939.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They quickly made it evident that his presence was not desired in Europe, and if he stayed very long, he might not even be in Europe or anywhere else.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, he was a lecturer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know that he did any classes, but he-- he turned up at the University of Chicago, which had all kinds of interesting people.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
